# Design Aesthetic

This project has a sleek, smooth, minimalist visual identity with an Apple-esque feel.

## Color

- **Primary palette**: Black and white dominate.
- **Emphasis**: Use deep, striking colors for accent, CTAs, and highlights — not pastels or muted tones.
- Keep backgrounds and surfaces mostly neutral (white, off-white, near-black) unless emphasizing something.
- Avoid mid-tones or muddied colors; use high contrast and clear hierarchy.

## Typography

- **Primary**: Sans-serif fonts only.
- Prefer clean, geometric sans-serifs (e.g. SF Pro–style, Inter, system UI fonts).
- Avoid serif and decorative fonts except where explicitly requested.
- Use weight and size for hierarchy rather than multiple typefaces.

## Visual Style

- **Sleek & smooth**: Generous whitespace, subtle shadows, soft transitions.
- **Minimalist**: No unnecessary decoration; every element should earn its place.
- **Apple-esque**: Clean lines, rounded corners where appropriate, refined interactions, premium feel.
- Avoid busy patterns, heavy borders, or cluttered layouts.
- Prefer subtle gradients or solid fills over complex visual effects.

## Implementation

- Reuse existing design tokens and variables first; align new styles with this system.
- When introducing colors, default to black/white/gray; use accent colors sparingly and intentionally.
- Test that emphasis elements stand out clearly against the minimal base.
